{"uid":"b4125b3767a85dd4","name":"[BUG-OT-006] TC-OT-014 — DELETE /api/v1/token: Must return 405 Method Not Allowed (returns 500)","fullName":"oauth-token-spr-fetcher-api.spec.ts:702:7","historyId":"46947820b5dd4d1db52369d4e919297d:0aa051a8bef16039484ddbf59137dd74","time":{"start":1783481252127,"stop":1783481312360,"duration":60233},"description":"**[KNOWN BUG — BUG-OT-006]**\n\n**What this test does:**\nSends a DELETE request to /api/v1/token (a GET-only endpoint — the DELETE endpoint is /api/v1/token/cache) and verifies the server returns 405 Method Not Allowed.\n\n**Expected:** HTTP 405 Method Not Allowed\n**Actual:** HTTP 500 Internal Server Error\n\n**Root Cause:** Same as BUG-OT-005 — unsupported methods trigger an unhandled exception in the service instead of a standard 405 response.\n\n**Additional Risk:** A client who mistypes the path and sends DELETE /api/v1/token instead of DELETE /api/v1/token/cache will receive a confusing 500 instead of a helpful 405 that would guide them to the correct endpoint.","descriptionHtml":"<p><strong>[KNOWN BUG — BUG-OT-006]</strong></p>\n<p><strong>What this test does:</strong><br />\nSends a DELETE request to /api/v1/token (a GET-only endpoint — the DELETE endpoint is /api/v1/token/cache) and verifies the server returns 405 Method Not Allowed.</p>\n<p><strong>Expected:</strong> HTTP 405 Method Not Allowed<br />\n<strong>Actual:</strong> HTTP 500 Internal Server Error</p>\n<p><strong>Root Cause:</strong> Same as BUG-OT-005 — unsupported methods trigger an unhandled exception in the service instead of a standard 405 response.</p>\n<p><strong>Additional Risk:</strong> A client who mistypes the path and sends DELETE /api/v1/token instead of DELETE /api/v1/token/cache will receive a confusing 500 instead of a helpful 405 that would guide them to the correct endpoint.</p>\n","status":"passed","flaky":false,"newFailed":false,"newBroken":false,"newPassed":false,"retriesCount":0,"retriesStatusChange":false,"beforeStages":[],"testSt